    {
      "id": 24,
      "lineId": 1,
      "beatId": 6,
      "bookId": 1,
      "positionWithinLine": 5,
      "positionInBeat": 6,
      "title": "<$n>) Cartel warns Bobby (first encounter) ",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "At the end of the night, Bobby packed up his gear. Halfway to his truck, one of the boss-lackeys called out, \"Bobby, let’s talk.\" He waved for Bobby to come into the motorhome. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Bobby looked at the rest of the guys already in the back of his truck waiting to go home. He shrugged at them. \"Hang on. This shouldn’t take too long.\" He had never been called to the motorhome before. His confident demeanor covered a multitude of fears. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "When he opened the door, four men crowded the motorhome. There was no chair for him. He stood in front of them. \"Close the door,\" said the foreman. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "His sweaty palm closed the door behind him. \"What- up?\" Dread rose from Bobby's stomach into his throat. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Where’s David?\" asked the Foreman. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The other three men Bobby didn’t recognize. Each sat in their fancy suits and ties with their arms crossed and legs splayed. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "What idiot wear’s a tie out here? "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Bobby thought. One wore glasses and should have had a pocket protector. Nerd. The big burley guy could eat the nerd for lunch with his gold tooth, gold jewelry, and dreadlocks. The third man, he exuded money and power. His suit, unlike the other two, was perfectly tailored in a material that shined even in this god-forsaken dust bowl."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"He took the night off,\" Bobby responded to the foreman, but kept one eye on the burley guy."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "All three men looked him up and down."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"You "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "vouched"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " for him.\" The Gold-man said. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Yea sure, but I didn’t guarantee he’d work every night. He’s feeling a bit under the weather, I think. A guy's got a right to have a night off, you know.\" The men sat silent as Bobby blathered on. \"Just needed some rest, that’s all.\" He took a breath. The silence hit his ears like bullets. Shut up, shut up. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Bobby broke. \"What’s the big deal?\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Sick, you say? Just needs rest?\" said the foreman. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Yea, yeah, that’s all. He’ll be back soon.\" The words slipped out. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Why the hell did I say that? "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Soon?\" The foreman looked to the Money Man who gave him a slight nod. \"Okay. You can leave.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"What?\" Bobby scanned the men but didn’t wait for an answer."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Before he could escape the Nerd asked, \"By the way, was that you on the old mine road yesterday about noon?"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Damn it all."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " Bobby had passed a car he didn’t recognize on the way out after dropping off Suzie at her truck. He figured they didn’t know him either, so didn’t give it much thought––there were trucks up and down this road all day; why would they think it was him? "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "{\\Scrv_annot \\color={\\R=0.54323\\G=0.0\\B=0.02382} \\text="
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Bobby move into Suzies house"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\\end_Scrv_annot}"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Yesterday? Noon? No, no, can’t say it was me. You know, I can’t imagine what I’d be doing out there during the day at all. There’s lots of trucks 'round these parts––\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The burley man stood. \"The man said, leave.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Cartel boss warns Bobby that he is accountable for David, who has not shown up for work, because Bobby brought him in. Bobby understands the threat. Introduce specific cartel men - boss, accountant, and muscle. \n"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [],
      "characters": [],
      "places": [],
