    {
      "id": 26,
      "lineId": 1,
      "beatId": 6,
      "bookId": 1,
      "positionWithinLine": 7,
      "positionInBeat": 6,
      "title": "<$n>) Cartel threatens Bobby (second encounter) ",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The foreman stood on the porch of the motorhome, arms crossed. Bobby kept an eye on him as he got out of the car. The foreman scanned the crowd, searched each man's face before moving to the next. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Bobby passed him, then glanced back to see the foreman glaring at Bobby."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "What's the big deal? Can't a guy take a night off?"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " Bobby avoided eye contact with the bossman."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Think he noticed David's not here?\" Bobby asked one of the guys who drove in with him. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Think your dick is big?\" Laugher broke out all around Bobby. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " \"Yea, yea. Funny. So funny. None of you better miss a day. You'll see then how funny it is...\" Bobby chatted non-stop to the surrounding men to ease his anxiety. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "At the end of the night, the men packed up their gear, and emerged from the mine when Bobby felt someone watching him. He looked up at a big man in a suit, with a gold tooth, and dreadlocks, his eyes set on Bobby. Lowering his head he quickened his pace, but was grabbed from behind. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Gold-man slammed Bobby at the feet of Dignified-man. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Bobby tried to scramble to his feet. Gold-man was there with a swift kick, followed by Dignified-man yanking Bobby up by his hair to within inches of Dignified-man's face, and jammed a gun under his chin. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"You "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "vouched"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " for him.\" Dignified-man had emphasized 'vouched' like a sacred blood oath. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"I'm sure he'll be here tomorrow.\" Bobby blurted, hoping to buy time. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Dignified-man pushed the gun in harder. \"Consider yourself warned.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The gun's muzzle pressed in hard enough to tilt Bobby's head back; the smell of vengeance bathed Dignified-man like a bad cologne. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Do you understand who I am––\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Gold-man bust into hysterics when he saw the dampness grow between Bobby's legs, causing Dignified-man to whisk the gun away from Bobby's chin, across Gold-man's jaw, and back again to Bobby. \"Never interrupt me,\" threatened Dignified-man. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Gold-man eyes lit up. His fists clenched for battle before a deep breath enabled him to calmed his shaking, but the hate in his eyes didn't quell. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Either David reports here in the next 48 hours,\" Dignified-man said to Bobby, \"or there will be consequences, and you know what they are.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "You"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " have my sister.\" Bobby responded more as a statement than a question. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Forty-eight hours.\" Dignified-man lowered his gun from Bobby's chin only long enough to swipe it across his face. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Scoffing, he pushed Bobby to the ground. \"Let this be a lesson to you all,\" Dignified-man lectured the other men looking on. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "In one smooth motion, he ejected the chambered bullet and tossed it onto Bobby."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Bobby dropped the last man off from the nightly escapade. He pulled his truck to the side of the road. \"Fuck. Fuck. Fuck.\" He pounded the steering wheel. He had barely held it together after he stopped to pick up David, pretended to wait for him, and feigned surprise when he didn’t show."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The bosses weren’t to happy when Bobby pulled in that night without David. Maybe it was Bobby's imagination, but the bosses overreacted. What was the big deal? No one was required to work every night. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "At the end of the night, they had packed up their gear and were heading out when one big man in a suit, with a gold tooth, and dreadlocks set his eyes on Bobby and pof the bosses yelled across the compound, \"Bobby, let’s talk.\" He waved for him to come into the motorhome. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Bobby looked at the rest of the guys already in the back of his truck wanting to go home.  He shrugged at them. \"Hang-on. This shouldn’t take too long.\" He had learned years ago that a confident demeanor covered a multitude of fears. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He had never been called to the motorhome before. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "When he had opened the door, four men crowded the motorhome. There was no chair for him.  He stood in front of them. \"Close the door,\" said the one known to the workers as the Foreman. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "His sweaty palm closed the door behind him. \"What- up?\" Bobby attempted to quell the dread rising from his stomach into his throat. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Where’s David?\" asked the Foreman. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The other three men, Bobby didn’t recognized. Each of them seated with their legs and arms crossed and wore fancy suits and ties. What idiot where’s a tie out here? One wore glasses and should have had a matching pocket protector. Nerd. The big burley guy looked like he could eat the nerd for lunch. The third man, he exuded money and power. His suit, unlike the other two, was perfectly tailored and the material shinned even in this god-forsaken dust bowl."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"He took the night off,\" Bobby responded to the Foreman but kept the burley guy in sight."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "All three men looked him up and down."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"You "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "vouched"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " for him.\" The Foreman emphasized vouched as if a blood oath.  "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Yea sure, but I didn’t guarantee he’d work every night.  He’s just feeling under the weather, I think. You know a guys got a right to have a night off, you know.\" The men sat silent and Bobby blathered on. \"Just needed some rest, that’s all.\" He took a breath. The silence hit his ears like bullets. Shut up, shut up.  "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"What’s the big deal?\" Bobby broke. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Sick you say? Just needs rest, ugh?\" said the Foreman. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Yea, yeah, that’s all. He’ll be back soon.\" The words slipped out. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Why the hell did I say that? "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Soon?\" The foreman looked to the Money Man who gave him a slight nod. \"Okay. You can leave.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"What?\" Bobby looked to each man but didn’t wait for an answer. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "But before he could escape the Nerd asked, \"By the way, was that you on the "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "{\\Scrv_annot \\color={\\R=0.54323\\G=0.0\\B=0.02382} \\text="
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "old mine road yesterday about noon?\""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\\end_Scrv_annot}"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Damn it all. Bobby had passed by a car he didn’t recognize on the way out after dropping Suzie off at her truck. He figured they didn’t know him either, so didn’t give it much thought––there were trucks up and down this road all day. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Ug, yesterday? Noon? No, no, can’t say it was me. You know, I can’t imagine what I’d be doing out there during the day and all. There’s lots of trucks 'round these parts––\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The burley name stood. \"The man said, leave.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Cartel threatens Bobby to produce David or die. Does this in front of the other men as a warning. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
