    {
      "id": 41,
      "lineId": 1,
      "beatId": 7,
      "bookId": 1,
      "positionWithinLine": 3,
      "positionInBeat": 8,
      "title": "<$n>) Aiden decides not to tell FBI about kidnapping ",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Angel busted through the front of Jeb's store with his head on a swivel. Aiden managed to catch his eye, and motioned for him to go around back. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "By the time Aiden got outside, Angel was, panting, pacing and wringing his hand."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"They took her. They took her. What do we do?\" Angel said tugging at Aiden's arm. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Whoa, Angel. Slow down.\" The calm in Aiden's voice seems to slow Angel down. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"The Cartel. They took Suzie.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"What? How? When?\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Angel told Aiden about the second threat that he helped deliver. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"I knew it was her,\" Aiden said. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"So Suzie thought they'd for sure deliver her Ma to the diner, but they got the jump on her instead.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"How long ago?\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"I ran right here, so no more than ten maybe 15 minutes? They tossed her in a dark blue Ford Pickup and drove in the direction of the mine.\""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Angel, you did great. Thank you. I'll take it from here. Now get out of here before someone see you.\""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Aiden arranged to meet Mrs. Jones at the garage. There he relayed what Angel had seen."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"I'm going to kill her if they don't.\" Aiden's face was flush, his veins pulsed. \"What are we going to do?\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"We've got to tell the FBI. Suzie's in serious trouble, and maybe her Ma too.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "{\\Scrv_annot \\color={\\R=0.54323\\G=0.0\\B=0.02382} \\text="
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "//Todo/confirm when Aiden finds out that Susie's Ma is dead "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\\end_Scrv_annot}"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Why should they believe us? There's no evidence they have either of them.\""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"You infiltrated the Cartel for them, to help them build a case. If there ever was a time to leverage your relationship, now is it. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\"No. No. They'll charge in––you saw the chaos they caused in town when they raided the cleaners, christ you would have thought they were breaking into Fort Knox––and before they even get within a half-mile of the motorhome their sentries will have sounded the alarm, and, for sure, they'll kill her and her Ma before the FBI set foot in the camp. No, I can't risk it.\" "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Angel tells Aiden about Suzie being kidnapped. Aiden and Mrs. Jones realize they have to loop in the FBI."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
